1.6.0 (Rust Edition) - 2026-05-01
    * COMPLETE REWRITE IN RUST:
        * Significant performance boost (~6x faster than C version, pushing 900k+ FPS).
        * Memory-safe rendering using Rust idiomatic patterns.
        * Pure Cargo build system (legacy Makefiles removed).
    * NEW FEATURES:
        * TrueColor Support: Added -T/--truecolor flag for 24-bit HD rendering.
        * Benchmark Mode: Added -b/--benchmark flag with 0ms delay for stress testing.
    * OPTIMIZATIONS:
        * Enabled LTO and aggressive release optimizations.
        * Pre-computed ANSI color palettes for faster rendering.
    * DOCUMENTATION:
        * Completely updated README.md and nyancat.1 man page.

---
Historical records for the original C implementation (v1.0 - v1.5.2)

1.5.2
    * Last official release of the original C version.

1.4.1
    * Fix telnet size negotiation

1.4
    * Added better terminal size autodetection
    * Fixed rendering when requested size was larger than
      available frame sizes
    * Made some corrections to the animation frames

1.3
    * Added option to skip intro in telnet mode

1.2.1
    * Fixes for manpage

1.2
    * Remove toaruos legacy support
    * Other minor fixes

1.1
    * Support various terminals (st, ToaruOS)
    * Changed color palette for 256 color modes
    * Added man page

1.0
    * Initial public release for packaging
